				Specific
			</button>
			<div id="content2">
				<ul>
					<li> Structured (zero-nonzero, sign pattern etc) inverse eigenvalue problems</li>
					<li> Signed graphs</li>
					<li> Centrality measures and clustering methods in neuroscience</li>
					<li> Minimum rank problems (symmetric, skew-symmetric, signed, positive semi-definite etc)</li>
					<li> Normal matrix compressions and their applications in numerical ranges and quantum computation</li>
					<li> Permanents and permanent rank problems</li>
					<li> Structure of cycles and matchings in graphs</li>
					<li> Applications of dynamical systems and graph theory in biology, neuroscience, economics, and mechanics</li>
					<li> Cospectral graphs, extremal problems in combinatorics, Ramanujan graphs</li>
				</ul>
