			<button class="togglebuttonh3"; onclick="toggleSlowly('content7')"> 
				Unpublished
			</button>
			<div id="content7">	
				<ol start="18">
					<li><b><a href="http://arxiv.org/pdf/1601.02760v1.pdf">Maximum multiplicity of eigenvalues of matrices with a given graph</a></b> <button class="togglebutton"; onclick="toggleSlowly('paper12')"> > Summary </button></li>Keivan Hassani Monfared and <a href="http://sudiptamallik.com/">Sudipta Mallik</a>: <a href="http://wcm.ucalgary.ca/k1monfared/files/k1monfared/the_maximum_multiplicty_of_an_eigenvalue_of_symmetric_matrices_with_a_given_graph.pdf">PDF</a>
						<div id="paper12">
						<ul class="borderedContent";>
							<li>For a graph \(G\), \(M(G)\) denotes the maximum multiplicity occurring of an eigenvalue of a symmetric matrix whose zero-nonzero pattern is given by edges of \(G\). Inspired by works of Duarte and Johnson, we introduce two combinatorial graph parameters \(T^âˆ’(G)\) and \(T^+(G)\) that give a lower and an upper bound for \(M(G)\) respectively, and we show that these bounds are sharp. This bound does not improve the already known zero forcing bound, hence it was seen unsuitable for publication.
					</li>
					</ul>
					</div>

				</ol>
			</div>
			
			</br>
